The course considers the interrelation and interaction between the Russian culture and the Russian language. The development and enrichment of the Russian language is traced in the historical-cultural context.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) to give the students an idea of "the language picture of the world" in the historical-cultural context; 2) to consider the most important topics concerning the culture and history of Russia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) has got knowledge which constitute the cultural heritage of a Russian person; 2) can analyse their own and other people's experience of communication with representatives of Russia and Russian culture; 3) can analyse scientific articles and other sources, find information about the country and write course papers; 4) has got experience of making a public presentation and working in a team; 5) can apply the knowledge about the country in planning lessons of Russian as foreign language.
